<!-- Coordinates:
Allowed radial coordinates: M_r_im1half[g](0), R_im1half[cm](1)
Allowed theta coordinates : theta_jm1half[rad](2)
Allowed phi coordinates   : phi_km1half[rad](3)
Allowed radial vectors (scalors in tp planes): U_im1halfjk[cm/s](4) , U0_im1half[cm/s](5)
Allowed theta vectors (scalors in rp planes) : V_ijm1halfk[cm/s](6)
Allowed phi vectors (scalors in rt planes)   : W_ijkm1half[cm/s](7)
Allowed Scalors :
D_ijk[g/cm^3](8)     , D_rel_dif_hor_ave(9)   , E_ijk[erg/g](10)      , E_rel_dif_hor_ave(11)  ,
T_ijk[K](12)         , T_rel_dif_hor_ave(13)  , P_ijk[dynes/cm^2](14) , P_rel_dif_hor_ave(15)  ,
Q_ijk[dynes/cm^2](16), Q_rel_dif_hor_ave(17)  , Kap_ij[cm^2/g](18)    , Kap_rel_dif_hor_ave(19),
Gam_ijk[na](20)      , Gam_rel_dif_hor_ave(21)

r from (0,0,0)
t measured from +z axis down
p in xy plane

Usefull geometric transforms for:

positions:
x =r*sin(t)*cos(p)
y =r*sin(t)*sin(p)
z =r*cos(t)

unit vectors:
r^= sin(t)*cos(p)*x^+sin(t)*sin(p)*y^+cos(t)*z^
t^= cos(t)*cos(p)*x^+cos(t)*sin(p)*y^-sin(t)*z^
p^=-       sin(p)*x^+       cos(p)*y^
-->
<!-- <figure></figure>
  title     : sets the title of the figure, \time will be replaced with the time \index will be 
              replaced with the time step index (number of time steps since the initial model).
  width     : width of the figure in inches
  height    : height of the figure in inches
  dpi       : dots per inches
  outputFile: Name of the output file(s). The suffix specifies the file type, supported file 
              types are .png, .pdf, .jpg, .gif-->
<figure title="$r-\phi$ slice at $j=11$, $t=$\time[s], time step=\index" width="12.0" height="3.0" dpi="150" outputFile="./slices_rt.png">
  
  <!-- <inputFileName></inputFileName>
    Name of the input file names including path. 
  -->
  <inputFileName>../output/3D_T5700_t[101000-102000]</inputFileName>
  
  <!-- RT-plane with combined u-u_0 and v vectors, transform: p=0, x->x, z->y
  <plane type="rt" index="0"></plane>
  <xaxis min="3.8e1" max="5.2e1" label="[$10^4$ km]">$1*sin($2)/1e10</xaxis>
  <yaxis min="-4e-1" max="5e-1" label="[$10^4$ km]">$1*cos($2)/1e10</yaxis>
  <scalor min="4e3" max="1e5" pallet="stellar" palletFocus="1e4" label="$T_{eff}$ [K]">$12</scalor>
  <vector color="k" xfrequency="5" yfrequency="1" scale="3">
    <label xpos="0.15" ypos="0.9">$(\mathbf{u}-\mathbf{u}_0+\mathbf{v}$) \scale [km/s]</label>
    <xposition>#1*sin(#2)/1e10</xposition>
    <yposition>#1*cos(#2)/1e10</yposition>
    <xcomponent>((#4-#5)*sin(#2)+#6*cos(#2))/1e5</xcomponent>
    <ycomponent>((#4-#5)*cos(#2)-#6*sin(#2))/1e5</ycomponent>
  </vector>-->
  
  
  <!-- RP-plane with combined u-u_0 and w vectors, transform: t=pi/2, x->x, y->y -->
  <plane type="rp" index="4"></plane>
  <xaxis min="44" max="52" label="[$10^4$ km]">$1*cos($3)/1e10</xaxis>
  <yaxis label="[$10^4$ km]">$1*sin($3)/1e10</yaxis>
  <scalor pallet="stellar" palletFocus="1e4" label="$T_{eff}$ [K]">$12</scalor>
  <vector color="k" xfrequency="4" yfrequency="1" scale="4.0">
    <label xpos="0.15" ypos="0.9">$\mathbf{v}$ \scale [km/s]</label>
    <xposition>#1*cos(#3)/1e10</xposition>
    <yposition>#1*sin(#3)/1e10</yposition>
    <xcomponent>((#4-#5)*cos(#3)+#7*sin(#3))/1e5</xcomponent>
    <ycomponent>((#4-#5)*sin(#3)+#7*cos(#3))/1e5</ycomponent>
  </vector>
  
  
  <!-- TP-plane with combined v and w vectors, transform, set let y->x, z->y
  <plane type="tp" index="304"></plane>
  <xaxis label="phi [cm]">#1*sin($2)*sin($3)</xaxis>
  <yaxis label="theta [cm]">#1*cos($2)</yaxis>
  <scalor pallet="jet" label="$T_{eff}$ [K]">$12</scalor>
  <vector color="k" scale="1.0">
    <label xpos="0.15" ypos="0.95">$\mathbf{w}$ \scale [km/s]</label>
    <xposition>#1*sin(#2)*sin(#3)</xposition>
    <yposition>#1*cos(#2)</yposition>
    <xcomponent>#6*cos(#2)*sin(#3)+#7*cos(#3)</xcomponent>
    <ycomponent>-1.0*#6*sin(#2)</ycomponent>
  </vector>-->
</figure>
